parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cruise control system can cause the vehicle to maintain speed even when the brakes are applied, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The cruise control system does not disengage when the brakes are applied
the vehicle continues to accelerate even when the brakes are applied
the cruise control system cannot be turned off
the vehicle takes a long time to come to a stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Warped brake rotors can cause the vehicle to vibrate, making it difficult to control, and can lead to increased stopping distances, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle vibrates when the brakes are applied
the vehicle takes longer to stop than usual.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause the brakes to lock up, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: the vehicle skids or loses traction
the ABS warning light comes on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause the vehicle to jerk forward, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: the engine accelerates even when the brakes are applied.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the driver's seat anchor can cause the seat to rock or come loose, leading to a loss of control while driving, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The driver's seat rocks or moves excessively
the seat comes unbolted from the floor
the seat comes off the track

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cooling system can cause the engine to overheat, leading to damage to the engine and other components, and potentially causing a loss of control or accident.
The defect in the engine block can restrict the flow of coolant, affecting the heater/defrost/cooling system, and potentially causing engine damage or failure.
The failure of the radiator can cause the engine to overheat, leading to damage to the engine and other components, and potentially causing a loss of control or accident.
A faulty combination switch can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power
the vehicle stops pulling or accelerating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Ignition system failure can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: the vehicle requires multiple attempts to start.
